hotflungwok wrote:Miso soup. It's healthy right? So I'll make some. It's easy. right?. I'll have some for dinner, then have a bunch of points for a drink or something later. It's all bs. I had a big bowl of it a little while ago, and now I'm hungrier. How the hell does having 4 cups of water & vegetables make you hungrier?Water absorbs quickly, vegetables don't get into blood as sugar for a while. Only satiety is fullness, which due to water, goes quickly.This phenomena is what makes clear soup a good appetizer. Now if you did a chili-esque thing full of beans and such, that should rate higher on the long term satiation scale.
