I'm fighting the 210 plateau. I use a FitBit One to track my activity and MyFitnessPal to track my food and I've been bouncing between 211 and 214 for a month. I've recently started ignoring the activity adjustment that FitBit injects and am just using my "base" calories of 1430 as a goal (sometimes putting me ~500 cals below the 1000 cal deficit I'm aiming for). No results, but I keep plugging away. Historically I'll see something like: 211, 211, 212, 211, 214, 211, 208 (wtf?), 209, 208. I'm psyched for 209 because that will put my total loss at 60lbs. I was getting very discouraged with the progress, but when I look at the lean mass / fat mass numbers over the last month it averages out to only 3 lbs on the scale, but 5 lbs of fat lost. I can live with that.
