Joining in on this thread to provide some accountability to my weight loss goals.8 years ago I weighed in at 285 and decided it was time to do something about it. Luckily for me just cutting the crap out of my diet basically took care of the issue. No more pop, candy, ice cream, or (and how I gained most of my weight) fluffy coffee drinks... and I drop to 205 within two years...Fast forward to 2 months ago I'm sitting at 210, a little older and trying to keep up with a crazy toddler who loves to run and play chase. I end up at the doctors for an unrelated issue and they decide to give me a basic blood workout to get some baselines on me. And uh oh... your blood sugar seems a bit high... could you go do another test for us please...And I come back with 11.2 a1c results?! Type 2 diabetes it is. Apparently I didn't change enough fast or far enough to avoid it, though I have no symptoms as of yet. /sigh So as a part of managing diabetes I need to lose weight, get active, and cut the carbs. I'm still sort of flailing about trying to find a balance of foods that I can eat to keep everything in check which started the current weight loss journey. I've dropped about 17 pounds since May(holy hell it seems like its been longer) and I'm now aiming for about 180 or probably a better guideline back to a 32-34 inch waist. Starting a C25K program to include that as part of the weight loss and D2 maintenance regime.Fin.
