HAHAHAHAHAHA! Fuck you, scale. 300.4lbs. I ended up doing a night-time walk, and did not bring enough water. I could feel my fingers puff up as my body started to retain extra water, and I do not drink a bunch after 9pm because I hate waking up to piss at night.I know that I could have just eaten clean on Saturday, and been below 300 for Sunday, but opted to keep my cheat day schedule. It just means one more week.With that out of the way, I continued my adventures in fall-down paddle boarding. I was practicing in the lake (salt lake? not sure what to call it) by my house. I found out that the middle of the lake is not really the deepest part when I fell in and sunk up to my shins in gooey mud. At least I did not go head first!So, I decided to jimmy the board onto the Tiburon, and did some surfing. At first I tried to get to clear water to try more fall-down practicing, but gave up because the waves just kept pounding me right off the board. Plus, as the high tide was coming in the water went from, 'OH MAN THAT FREEZES THE BALLS... oh, not so bad', to, 'HOLY CRAP I CAN'T FEEL MY NOSE ANYMORE'. It was still fun as hell riding a nice big board on those massive waves. I can only imagine how much fun it will be to actually stand up and surf them.Oh yes, surf wax is great for being able to stay on the board, but sucks ass when you are trying to drag yourself back on after falling off.
