Crombie wrote:HAHAHAHAHAHA! Fuck you, scale. 300.4lbs. I ended up doing a night-time walk, and did not bring enough water. I could feel my fingers puff up as my body started to retain extra water, and I do not drink a bunch after 9pm because I hate waking up to piss at night.Your fingers don't swell because of fluid retention.It's more likely blood. Your blood vessels dilate during exercise and the muscles in your arms don't work very hard to "squeeze" the blood back to your heart (as compared to your legs).
