Well, because of bad (but wonderfully delicious) choices over the last two months, I’m up 10lb, now at around 215. Hopefully, now that I’m on a mission to lose what I’ve gained, I will drop those 10 quickly, and continue past 205, where I’ve been stuck for some time.Here are two questions since there are knowledgeable people in the thread:1. I do about one hour of cardio a day. Would it be helpful to get any of those protein shakes or whatever to drink after that hour? Would there be any benefits for my goal, which is dropping weight? Or, should I just stick with water?2. May be unrelated to the topic of the thread. Does anyone have suggestions about vitamin supplements for men? I figure since I am trying to take better care of myself, I may as well look into it. Also, a body that is getting everything that it needs may be more amicable to losing fat (well, it makes sense in my head).
