Hopers wrote:I have a two-pronged problem... my scale broke, and I've been lazy about tracking calories. The scale was a withings scale. I loved it, but I was not happy with their customer service when it broke. It's also going to be rather pricey to replace. I should probably be annoyed that a $150 scale broke after 3 years, but my husband tripped over it more than once, so I don't blame the poor thing for breaking. I've also been bad (terrible) about tracking calories. I tend to get to a point where I'm burnt out on doing it, and I'm at that point.My saving grace is that I'm currently in "you have no idea what your weight is doing, so no slip-ups" mode. I'm not letting myself eat any junk and I've been really mindful about not snacking too much and eating smaller portions. For shortish periods of time, this actually tends to work really well for me.I have a coupon for $40/off a new scale, so I think I'm going to order myself a new one. I know I can get the same info from a $20 scale, but I really like the accountability I get with the withings.I have this one: https://www.fitbit.com/ariaI like it a lot. I get in the biggest trouble when I 1) Don't track my weight, 2) Don't track my calories. This completely solves #1 for me.
