I ended up buying the newer version of my withings scale. The OCD part of me wanted to keep everything on the same system, with the same historic trend. Vafarmboy, my basic strategy is careful eating on weekdays. Then, I have one weekend day where I mostly try to eat well, but I don't fuss about it too much. And one weekend day is a cheat day and I eat whatever I want. Which is basically your strategy as well. If I don't eat well during the week, I don't give myself the cheat day. It seems to work fairly well for me. It's also good to be able to say during the week "don't eat that now, you're going to have ice cream on Sunday." If we're planning something for the weekend that I know will involve a fair amount of pigging out, I make sure that's my cheat day as well. Turbo2
